import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.scatterplot(data=data, x='u', y='v')
    plt.title('What is the correlation between u and v?', wrap=True)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

```
import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.boxplot(data=data[['u', 'v']])
    plt.title('What is the range of values for u and v?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('u and v')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

```
import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='u', kde=True, color='blue')
    plt.axvline(data['u'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f"Mean: {data['u'].mean():.2f}")
    plt.axvline(data['u'].median(), color='green', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f"Median: {data['u'].median():.2f}")
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the distribution of u?', wrap=True)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.lineplot(data=data, x='u', y='v', hue=data.index, palette='viridis')
    plt.title('What is the relationship between u and v across different samples?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('u')
    plt.ylabel('v')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
